text.tspan: Number of Workers by Income and Sector
The purpose of this project is to investigate how the income inequality of Chinese waged
workers is related to the industries that they work in. On the left is a histogram representing the
wage distribution within each industry. On the top is a stacked bar chart/bump chart hybrid
representing the number of surveyed workers in each industrial sector at each income range.
It can be observed that very few people work in the primary sector and that they usually have
very low wages. People working in finance, technical service, and IT tend to have the highest
wages. However, tertiary sector constitutes the majority of low income workers, while
secondary sector makes up most of the medium to high income workers.
Data source: CFPS (China Family Panel Studies) 2018 survey
